      <h1>CCL Multi-Layer Board Roller Cleaner: Selection Guide &amp; Efficiency Optimization — Technical Q&amp;A</h1>
      <p class="blog-lead">
        Selecting a roller adhesive cleaner for copper-clad laminate multi-layer board production is not simply a procurement decision — it is a direct lever on press-lamination yield, production line OEE, and long-term operating cost. Dust and fiber contamination present at the lamination step cause voids, delamination, and signal integrity failures that no downstream process can recover. Yet selection decisions are frequently made on price alone, and efficiency problems are addressed reactively rather than systematically. This guide answers the questions that CCL and multi-layer PCB manufacturers ask most often, and provides answers grounded in production realities rather than specification sheets.
      </p>

